cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about unsupervised text style transfer, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new framework that utilizes gradients for optimization, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a variational auto-encoder (VAE) and predictors, which are common tools in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the manipulation of sentence length and the presence of specific words, which could involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's use of gradient-based optimization suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
